  "body": "### Preamble\r\nTitle: pay gas with tokens directly\r\nAuthor: Xu (@acvrp-lab)\r\nType: Standards Track\r\nCategory: ERC\r\nStatus: Draft\r\nCreated: 2020-10-19\r\nRequires: ERC20\r\n### Simple Summary\r\nAllow mining node to accept a list of standard tokens of its preference as gas fees.\r\nAllow user to pay from a list of standard tokens of its preference as gas fees directly.\r\n### Motivation\r\nI'm a newbie in the crypto industry, learning all kinds of new concepts. meta transaction, GSN(gas station network), smart wallet, DAI's gasless wallet, all to solve one problem - to pay gas with tokens. however, they add quite much complexity, security concerns, user need to pay extra reward to incentivize relayers.\r\nSo how about a client patch to allow gas fees to be payed with tokens directly?\r\n### Specification & Implementation\r\nThis seems to be quite out of reach of a newbie's ability.\r\nHowever, to my assumption, there's no need to fork, change anything to the chain mechanism, evm or other big components.\r\n1. token contract patch to allow miner to transfer token at user specified gas price\r\n2. mining node client patch to accept tokens of its preference\r\n3. wallet apps(i've only used metamask till now) patch to allow user to pay with tokens just like how they pay with ether\r\n\r\nif this proposal is ever impelemented, I assume stablecoins will become the most used paying tokens",
