    "body": "after some thought, i assume i've come up with an implementation with the most backward compatibility.\r\n### 1. contract of token user used to pay gas need to add one function. below is some pseudo-code\r\n```\r\nfunction gasless(address to, data, price-in-token) {\r\n  var limit = gasleft();\r\n  make-original-transaction{value: msg.value}(to, data);\r\n  transfer(block.coinbase, (limit - gasleft() + extra to execute this line) * price-in-token);\r\n}\r\n```\r\nan old transaction is a serialized message of {nonce, gas price, gas limit, recipient, value, data, sig A}\r\na gasless transaction is now {nonce, gas price=0, gas limit(a little bigger than previous), recipient=paying token, value, data =call to new gasless function, sig B}\r\n\r\n### 2. mining node client:\r\nold ones will still work, and can verify gasless transactions with no problems. only that it has nearly no chance to process 0 gas price transactions. if it does, it will receive fee in token just like updated clients.\r\nupdated clients will process gasless transactions just like old style transactions, compare gas price in ether/token, prioritize their prefered transactions. the more updated clients, it is more likely gasless txs will be processed.\r\n\r\n### 3. wallet apps:\r\neven old ones can run with some work from user or dapp developer, it is better to update for better user experience.",
